[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-16T17:48:19+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Image showing Mike Tyson, mid-punch as Jake Paul dodges.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/5zggMTXjCMWg8hoQYCkhkWp15ak=/0x0:2000x1333/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73727908/AB4_6911_Q2mnYmjN.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Netflix had a very big night.</em> | Photo: Al Bello / Getty Images for Netflix</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"oxxR1I\">Netflix peaked at \u201c65 million concurrent streams\u201d during the boxing match between Mike Tyson and Jake Paul last night, according to Most Valuable Promotions, the promoter for the fight. Those streams went out to 60 million households globally, the group said in a press release shared with <em>The Verge </em>via email. That\u2019s more than <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usatoday.com%2Fstory%2Fsports%2F2023%2F12%2F28%2Fnfl-ratings-dominate-nba-on-christmas%2F72052196007%2F&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thev", "id": 1528227, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/16/24298338/netflix-mike-ttyson-vs-jake-paul-fight-netflix-60-million-households-streaming-quality-buffering", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "60 million households watched the Tyson vs. Paul fight on Netflix", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-16T17:24:47+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Graphic illustration of the eagle from the dollar bill with the shape of a smart phone instead of a shield.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/KybIdzukIeZk8HKTShi0sgVNSoY=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73727876/STK481_STK432_CONGRESS_GOVERNMENT_CIVRGINIA_A.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Cath Virginia / The Verge; Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"SJYDf3\">Complaints about unwanted telemarketing calls have dropped for the third straight year, the <a href=\"https://www.ftc.gov/news-events/news/press-releases/2024/11/reports-unwanted-telemarketing-calls-down-more-50-percent-2021\">Federal Trade Commission announced</a> yesterday. Reports of such calls have fallen by over 50 percent versus 2021, according to the FTC \u2014 a decline that could be thanks in no small part to stepped-up government efforts to fight irritating telemarketing and phone scams.</p>\n<p id=\"cdfMA1\">There were about 33,000 fewer un", "id": 1528228, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/16/24298278/ftc-illegal-scam-call-robocall-telemarketer-complaints-down-50-percent-since-2021", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The FTC says spam call complaints are way down since 2021", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-16T15:38:47+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Apple Watch, Garmin Epix, Fitbit, and Amazfit Bip fitness trackers on a stylized blue background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/9NfU5CzAkm1H45234kKpT8gicKk=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/70657030/acastro_220321_5092_0001.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>From simple fitness bands and rugged sports watches to rings, these are the best trackers you can get.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/22985108/best-fitness-tracker\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>\n\n", "id": 1528003, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/22985108/best-fitness-tracker", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The best fitness trackers to buy right now", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-16T15:00:21+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo collage of various MagSafe chargers.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/2w7Phksq07lEVBqIRIJ_oasnPkg=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/71769681/247290_Buying_Guide_MagSafe_Charger_CVirginia.6.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Cath Virginia / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Thanks to Qi2, there are way more great chargers for your MagSafe phone than ever before.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23505846/best-magsafe-magnetic-chargers-apple-iphone\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>\n\n", "id": 1527871, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23505846/best-magsafe-magnetic-chargers-apple-iphone", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The best MagSafe and Qi2 chargers for your iPhone", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-16T13:19:51+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Narwal\u2019s Freo X Ultra against the wall.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/mScZ9fHVDdzCTEcxuUhEEfTO0cQ=/0x0:5137x3425/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73727586/8A0A1086.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Freo X Ultra packs a lot of features for the price, including the ability to automatically remop your floors when necessary.</em> | Photo by Jennifer Pattison Tuohy / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"yvVOYm\">Hosting Thanksgiving dinner is fun and all, but the amount of cleaning you have to do afterward can be exhausting. The <strong>Narwal Freo X Ultra</strong> robot vacuum / mop hybrid can help speed things up, though, and it\u2019s currently down to an all-time low of $849.99 (about $690 off) at <a href=\"https://howl.link/v1t43gmm5nsbh\">Best Buy</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0CPLP422K?tag=theverge02-20\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Amazon</a> (when you apply the on-page coupon).</", "id": 1527470, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/16/24297331/narwal-freo-x-ultra-robot-vacuum-mop-sony-wh-1000xm4-deal-sale", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Narwal\u2019s Freo X Ultra, the best mopping robot available, is on sale for a new low price", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-16T12:55:24+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot of concept art showing four people running toward the top of what appears to be a submarine, poking through ice.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/SROttn2th-IjUyWLG05CAFEsW94=/0x27:1452x995/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73727543/Screenshot_2024_11_16_at_11.47.41_AM.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Concept art for </em>Half-Life 2: Episode 3<em>, from the </em>Half-Life 2<em> 20th Anniversary Documentary.</em> | Screenshot: YouTube</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"kMHJap\">Unsurprisingly, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/15/24297691/half-life-2-20th-anniversary-update-documentary\">yesterday\u2019s big <em>Half-Life</em> release</a> wasn\u2019t the sequel to <em>Half-Life 2 </em>or even the third <em>Half-Life 2: Episode</em> entry, but a 20th-anniversary update to Valve\u2019s legendary 2004 game. And given what studio co-founder Gabe Newell has to say on the subject in a <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YCj", "id": 1527471, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/16/24298091/gabe-newell-half-life-2-documentary-why-hl-3-never-happened", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Gabe Newell says Half-Life 2: Episode 3 didn\u2019t happen because he was \u2018stumped\u2019", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-16T10:11:17+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/DtsouSWO2gSkpZxiuKasLBTfcS8=/0x58:2000x1391/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73727313/SS2_0106_eWtsAlhn.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption>Getty Images for Netflix \u00a9 2024</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"bIdSde\">Netflix\u2019s livestream of the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/31/24169091/netflix-mike-tyson-jake-paul-boxing-rescheduled\">Mike Tyson and Jake Paul boxing match</a> was a mess. I\u2019m not talking about the bout itself \u2014 although people <a href=\"https://www.forbes.com/sites/danidiplacido/2024/11/16/mike-tyson-vs-jake-paul-was-an-entertaining-disaster/\">had their qualms with that</a>, too \u2014 it\u2019s the livestream, which people across the internet complained was plagued by buffering, unstable, and unwatchable muddiness. That doesn\u2019t bode well for Netflix\u2019s live sports ambitions, especially its <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/15/24157289/netflix-nfl-game-streaming-global-christmas", "id": 1526797, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/16/24298026/mike-tyson-jake-paul-netflix-livestream-quality-issues-buffering-dropped-stream", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "NFL fans worry Netflix\u2019s bad Tyson vs. Paul stream means it can\u2019t handle football", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-16T10:00:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vector illustration showing various aspects of the Bluesky app.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/d6LqwlX374aijYLmPDDMZUcXyoQ=/0x0:3000x2000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73727284/HT057_BLUESKY_CVirginia_A.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Samar Haddad / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"y4RPKb\">So, you\u2019ve finally decided to give Bluesky a shot. The social network has come a long way since the early bare-bones days of <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/2/28/23619270/decentralized-twitter-alternative-bluesky-ios-invite-only\">invite-only signups</a> and recently grew <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/13/24295484/bluesky-15-million-users-social-media-x-musk\">past the 15 million user mark</a>. Along the way, it\u2019s gathered a lot of familiar posting platform features, like <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/22/24162749/bluesky-send-direct-messages\">direct messages</a>, <a href=\"https://www.theverge", "id": 1526798, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24295933/bluesky-social-network-custom-how-to", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Here\u2019s some cool stuff you can do with Bluesky", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-16T08:00:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot from The Rise of the Golden Idol.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/5PH-PFh3LLeLfmkeCNq6fVLgaFo=/257x0:1877x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73727106/ss_d07481f7aae963c3135529b4d96053f13359d947.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Playstack / Color Gray Games</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"85sNOs\"><em>The Case of the Golden Idol</em> was <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23433741/the-case-of-the-golden-idol-review-pc\">a rewarding series of point-and-click murder mysteries</a> that became one of my favorite games of 2022. And while I felt there was more story to explore about the titular golden idol, I wasn\u2019t sure if a potential sequel could live up to its clever puzzles and fascinating, slowly unfolding story. Turns out, I had nothing to fear: <em>The Rise of the Golden Idol</em>, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/10/24267159/the-rise-of-the-golden-idol-release-date-trailer\">the newly launched seq", "id": 1526354, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24295956/the-rise-of-the-golden-idol-review-pc-playstation-xbox-netflix-mobile", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Rise of the Golden Idol makes a great puzzle game even better", "vote": 0}]